=== The `bsky.posts` Table

The `posts` table is a normalised extract of `app.bsky.feed.post` records. It contains $28.1 times 10^6$ rows with columns `did`, `rkey`, `time_us`, `created_at`, `post_text`, `lang`, and reply-chain fields (`reply_root_uri`, `reply_parent_uri`).

- *Top-level posts* (`reply_root_uri IS NULL`): $15.3 times 10^6$ (54.4%) — original content that starts a new thread or stands alone.
- *Replies* (`reply_root_uri IS NOT NULL`): $12.8 times 10^6$ (45.6%) — responses within existing threads.

Language coverage is dominated by English (60.8%), followed by Japanese (10.6%), Portuguese (2.8%), German (2.8%), and Spanish (2.6%). Approximately 11.7% of posts have no language tag.

Due to an unfortunate processing event, quote-posts are currently absent from `bsky.posts` because the dump pipeline did not extract the `record.embed` field. A spot-check of the raw firehose shows ~5.6% of posts are quote-posts. These are misclassified as plain posts or replies. This is a known limitation of the database dump, not of the analysis.

=== The `bsky.records` Table

The `records` table is a comprehensive dump of almost all the AT Protocol record events. It contains $212.5 times 10^6$ rows, with operations dominated by `create` (96.9%), followed by `delete` (2.7%) and `update` (0.4%).

The three dominant record types account for 97.3% of all records, as can be seen in @tbl-records-collections.

